				"start": 0,
				"end": 728,
				"data": " An empty block-body element inside <pre> that overflows. The wrapped attributes and close token indent off the element's nesting depth (one level per enclosing container, matching prettier), and the source close form is preserved: self-closing keeps `/>`, explicit-empty keeps its close tag. When the attributes fit within print width they stay on one line and only the close token drops to its own line; when they overflow they wrap one per line with `/>` on its own line, never hugging the last attribute. The divergence is print-width-as-hard-limit: output_prettier shows prettier full-breaking the self-closing elements' attributes even though they fit (the explicit-empty and overflowing cases now match prettier). "
